WEBVTT

00:01.873 --> 00:03.686
Contagious.

00:03.707 --> 00:05.473
We must contain this pandemic.

00:05.475 --> 00:06.941
[coughing, retching]

00:06.943 --> 00:09.310
- Contagious.
- Contagious.

00:09.312 --> 00:10.612
- Contagious.
- Contagious.

00:10.614 --> 00:11.780
- Contagious.
- Contagious.

00:11.782 --> 00:12.947
- [crying]
<i>- Contagious.</i>

00:12.949 --> 00:15.984
<i>[soft piano music]</i>

00:15.986 --> 00:21.823
<i>♪</i> ♪

00:21.825 --> 00:24.759
Everyone stay back! Stay back, damn you!

00:24.761 --> 00:26.027
[door slams shut]

00:28.231 --> 00:31.332
Excuse me, sir, but I'm afraid we must

00:31.334 --> 00:32.834
quarantine the downstairs.

00:32.836 --> 00:35.737
We're having a tiny outbreak situation.

00:35.739 --> 00:38.973
The cook and staff have
"beshitted" most of the kitchen.

00:38.975 --> 00:41.276
Oh, those poor people!

00:41.278 --> 00:43.077
You mean, "Oh, those <i> poor</i> people."

00:43.079 --> 00:44.779
I'm telling you, Daddy, it's high time

00:44.781 --> 00:46.514
we got one of those
modern, new flamethrowers

00:46.516 --> 00:48.750
and burnt that
whole downstairs to a crisp.

00:48.752 --> 00:50.285
Maybe then they can make a crème brûlée

00:50.287 --> 00:52.287
- that doesn't taste like snot!
- [dish shatters]

00:52.289 --> 00:54.122
How can you think about dessert

00:54.124 --> 00:55.690
at a time like this?

00:55.692 --> 00:56.991
I just finished my entree,

00:56.993 --> 00:58.301
what else am I supposed to think about?

00:58.303 --> 01:01.196
Well, as a proud "Grey Lady"
of the Red Cross

01:01.198 --> 01:03.865
Volunteers Corp,
I'll be going downstairs

01:03.867 --> 01:05.834
to save those poor souls.

01:05.836 --> 01:07.368
Well, the only thing
I'm interested in saving

01:07.370 --> 01:09.370
is the family fortune
and my rear virginity...

01:09.372 --> 01:10.805
for second marriage. [giggles]

01:10.807 --> 01:12.473
That's my baby girl. [clears throat]

01:12.475 --> 01:15.310
Peepers, whatever we do,
lets do it quietly.

01:15.312 --> 01:18.213
I'm afraid the Lookie-Loos
already sniffing about.

01:18.215 --> 01:19.914
The newspaper's here?

01:19.916 --> 01:21.416
<i>[upbeat string music]</i>

01:21.418 --> 01:24.152
Well, then, lets save these
poor souls in their final hours!

01:24.154 --> 01:27.222
The last thing those poor people need

01:27.224 --> 01:29.691
- is you, Lillian!
- No, I'm going to do that.

01:29.693 --> 01:31.059
The last thing they need is you!

01:31.061 --> 01:34.429
Your disease is more
rampant than theirs is!

01:34.431 --> 01:37.165
- I am certified to deal with it!
- I'm winning.

01:37.167 --> 01:39.567
<i>♪ I want the money, I want the fame ♪</i>

01:39.569 --> 01:42.003
<i>♪ I want the whole world
to know my name ♪</i>

01:42.005 --> 01:44.339
<i>♪ This is mine, I got to get it ♪</i>

01:44.341 --> 01:46.841
<i>♪ I got to get it, got, got to get it ♪</i>

01:46.843 --> 01:48.109
<i>♪ "Another Period" ♪</i>

01:48.147 --> 01:52.136
Synced & corrected by -robtor-
www.addic7ed.com

01:52.215 --> 01:55.116
[crickets chirping]

01:59.522 --> 02:01.222
How are you sleeping?

02:01.224 --> 02:02.891
- [both scream]
- Kill him first!

02:02.893 --> 02:04.492
Identify yourself, state your price

02:04.494 --> 02:06.661
and then write to my father
and ask him for that price!

02:06.663 --> 02:08.463
Frederick, it's me.

02:09.566 --> 02:12.200
[gasps] Oh, hello, Beatrice.

02:12.202 --> 02:14.168
I was just having
the most delicious dream

02:14.170 --> 02:16.537
about a bear with human hands.

02:16.539 --> 02:18.339
[scoffs] What the hell
are you doing here?

02:18.341 --> 02:20.308
Well, I wanted to tell you
the good news.

02:20.310 --> 02:23.278
Father set me up with a suitor
and I think I like him.

02:23.280 --> 02:25.613
You travelled 12 hours by train,

02:25.615 --> 02:27.582
broke into our house, into our room,

02:27.584 --> 02:29.617
and all that just to say
you met someone?

02:29.619 --> 02:31.085
No, that's ridiculous.

02:31.087 --> 02:33.421
We travelled by carriage
and it took two weeks.

02:33.423 --> 02:36.090
Anyway, his name is Dick
and he's the president

02:36.092 --> 02:37.425
of the Pinta Yacht Club.

02:37.427 --> 02:39.193
- He's the president?
- Mm-hmm.

02:39.195 --> 02:41.129
Darn it, I'm only the vice president.

02:41.131 --> 02:43.231
You're vice president
of the United States.

02:43.233 --> 02:45.099
You don't have to rub it in my face.

02:45.101 --> 02:47.368
All right, enough, Beatrice,
it's time for you to leave.

02:47.370 --> 02:49.270
Freddie has got a country to run.

02:49.272 --> 02:50.872
Ohh, okay. Bye, Beatrice.

02:50.874 --> 02:53.574
Well, can't wait to meet
your new friend.

02:53.576 --> 02:56.344
- Now, ta-ta.
- You mean it, Celery?

02:56.346 --> 02:59.047
- A double date?
- Uh, not... not really.

02:59.049 --> 03:00.311
We can do it tonight!

03:00.313 --> 03:02.050
I'm at the hotel
across from the penis monument.

03:02.052 --> 03:04.419
Oh, Beatrice, I made a similar mistake.

03:04.421 --> 03:07.221
It's actually called
the Washington Penis.

03:07.223 --> 03:09.390
Oh, okay. Celery...

03:09.392 --> 03:11.125
you're the best sister in the world!

03:11.127 --> 03:13.061
Okay. Oh, no. Oh... ohh.

03:13.063 --> 03:14.862
I'll see you tonight.

03:14.864 --> 03:16.159
Bye, Freddie.

03:16.900 --> 03:19.540
Did she say you were
officially sisters now?

03:20.403 --> 03:22.437
<i>[gloomy music]</i>

03:22.439 --> 03:23.938
[coughing]

03:23.940 --> 03:27.442
<i>♪</i> ♪

03:27.444 --> 03:30.345
May God bless you
and keep you, my child.

03:30.347 --> 03:32.580
Heiress coming through. [laughs]

03:32.582 --> 03:34.282
Oh, if it isn't Brussels Sheridan

03:34.284 --> 03:36.351
of the Lookie-Loos Society Pages.

03:36.353 --> 03:38.319
If it isn't Lillian Bellacourt.

03:38.321 --> 03:40.922
Would you like to get
a few photographic stills of me?

03:40.924 --> 03:42.123
I could grab one of these near dead

03:42.125 --> 03:43.825
in the better lighting. Oh, yes!

03:43.827 --> 03:45.626
Excuse me, we're taking a picture!

03:45.628 --> 03:47.795
- [pounds on glass]
- Lady of the house speaking.

03:47.797 --> 03:49.464
Everyone come close,
we're gonna do a little

03:49.466 --> 03:51.032
"photo-graph."

03:51.034 --> 03:52.667
Oh. Oh!

03:52.669 --> 03:54.769
- On three.
- All right, everyone, ready?

03:54.771 --> 03:57.772
One, two, three!

03:57.774 --> 03:58.950
[shutter clicks]

03:59.809 --> 04:01.175
- Un, deux...
- [snapping fingers]

04:01.177 --> 04:02.777
un, deux, trois, quatre.

04:02.779 --> 04:05.246
- [all singing]
- ♪ Wade in the water ♪

04:05.248 --> 04:07.849
♪ Wade in the water ♪

04:07.851 --> 04:10.485
♪ Wade in the water ♪

04:10.487 --> 04:12.787
♪ God's gonna trouble the water ♪

04:12.789 --> 04:15.156
- ♪ Now wade in that water ♪
- He's doing it again!

04:15.158 --> 04:16.357
- He's doing it again!
- What?

04:16.358 --> 04:18.026
- Hello. Hello.
- What'd I do?

04:18.028 --> 04:21.728
Stop manjacking like a bunch
of Baltimore Slavics.

04:21.731 --> 04:23.765
We are the Gentlemen Callers, please.

04:23.767 --> 04:25.700
The Boston Barber-Fest is next week.

04:25.702 --> 04:27.835
It's where the Dandy Dollops
got their start!

04:27.837 --> 04:30.505
That's why I suggest that I do the solo

04:30.507 --> 04:33.141
because I am the face
of contemporary barber shop.

04:33.143 --> 04:36.177
You are the face of a sad
and pathetic man.

04:36.179 --> 04:37.841
Oh, well, in that case,
I'm the face of you.

04:38.314 --> 04:39.521
[stammers]

04:39.849 --> 04:44.352
<i>[hip-hop music]</i>

04:44.354 --> 04:47.155
So how exactly did you two meet again?

04:47.157 --> 04:48.890
Oh, it's such a funny story.

04:48.892 --> 04:50.591
- Do you want to tell it?
- No, you tell it.

04:50.593 --> 04:52.860
- Okay, we'll both tell it.
- Yes. [giggles]

04:52.862 --> 04:54.395
The Commodore was doing a business deal

04:54.397 --> 04:56.197
with my father, Admiral Firestone...

04:56.199 --> 04:58.733
Mm-hmm and he thought I would
make a fruitful bargaining chip.

04:58.735 --> 05:01.602
So, as luck would have it,
he said that in exchange

05:01.604 --> 05:04.005
for my family's oil rights
in Nova Scotia...

05:04.007 --> 05:05.540
Commodore would give him his opal mines,

05:05.542 --> 05:08.242
$750,000 worth of gold bullion...

05:08.244 --> 05:11.679
And his tallest daughter
who just happens to be...

05:11.681 --> 05:14.382
- both: Beatrice!
- [both laugh]

05:14.384 --> 05:17.118
My father heard that and he said, "Sold!

05:17.120 --> 05:21.086
both: "You can't put a price
on opal these days."

05:21.724 --> 05:25.093
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:25.095 --> 05:26.761
[groans]

05:26.763 --> 05:27.998
I hate water.

05:28.598 --> 05:30.038
Tastes like my mouth.

05:30.433 --> 05:32.700
[sighs]

05:32.702 --> 05:35.136
- [clinks on window]
- [splashes]

05:35.138 --> 05:36.754
Next!

05:38.141 --> 05:39.540
[screams]

05:39.542 --> 05:41.476
Get out of here, Lillian!

05:41.478 --> 05:43.711
- You're burning the servants.
- No,

05:43.713 --> 05:45.546
I'm the one who's gonna slop these hogs.

05:45.548 --> 05:48.649
There's a typhoid epidemic
going on here, Lillian,

05:48.651 --> 05:51.385
- so I suggest you move over.
- No!

05:51.387 --> 05:53.554
I'm more compassionate
than you, you sloth..

05:53.556 --> 05:56.457
[laughs] The sloth is the gentlest

05:56.459 --> 05:59.460
of the South American Pilosa
genus of placental mammals.

05:59.462 --> 06:01.896
So I'll take it as a compliment.

06:01.898 --> 06:04.465
Take it however you wish, just move!

06:04.467 --> 06:06.134
Oh, you like to push?

06:06.136 --> 06:09.937
How about a push
from a certified Grey Lady?

06:09.939 --> 06:11.973
[screams] [both grunting]

06:11.975 --> 06:14.775
Contagious! Contagious!

06:14.777 --> 06:17.678
Everyone, hold your breath!

06:17.680 --> 06:19.747
[whimpers]

06:19.749 --> 06:22.250
- Infected patient...
- No!

06:22.252 --> 06:25.052
Please step behind the partition.

06:25.054 --> 06:26.387
No, no, if I'm going to be infected,

06:26.389 --> 06:27.822
it would be from
a rich person's disease.

06:27.824 --> 06:30.291
Like gold poisoning
or a governor's rash,

06:30.293 --> 06:31.959
not... not typhoid.

06:31.961 --> 06:34.195
Contagious. Contagious.

06:34.197 --> 06:35.229
[whimpers]

06:37.620 --> 06:40.187
So, what I'm dying to know is

06:40.189 --> 06:41.670
how did you two meet?

06:42.291 --> 06:44.391
Fredrick, would you
like to tell the story?

06:44.393 --> 06:46.327
No, it's boring and I don't remember it.

06:47.597 --> 06:49.396
Oh, soup! [chuckles]

06:51.601 --> 06:54.535
Aah! Hot! Hot! Mouth!

06:54.537 --> 06:55.736
[groaning]

06:55.738 --> 06:58.183
Ooh, soup fools me every time. [sighs]

06:58.708 --> 07:01.208
You know I feel a bit
of a headache coming on.

07:01.210 --> 07:03.410
Perhaps I'll go walk the gardens.

07:03.412 --> 07:06.580
- Get some fresh air.
- Okay, bye.

07:06.582 --> 07:08.318
[clears throat]

07:08.920 --> 07:11.051
Oh! Can I have your dessert

07:11.053 --> 07:12.551
if it gets here before you come back?

07:12.888 --> 07:14.151
[sighs]

07:14.924 --> 07:16.206
Excuse me.

07:19.228 --> 07:21.740
Should someone go and check
and see if she's unwell?

07:21.765 --> 07:23.464
Oh, I would, but I don't want to miss

07:23.466 --> 07:25.570
my soup at its ideal temperature.

07:26.102 --> 07:28.569
I'll just go check
and see how she's doing.

07:28.571 --> 07:29.870
Okay, bye.

07:33.843 --> 07:36.110
Aah! Still hot!

07:36.112 --> 07:37.945
Still so hot! Come here.

07:37.947 --> 07:41.482
- [panting]
- [blowing]

07:41.484 --> 07:43.517
- Better?
- Uhhuh.

07:43.519 --> 07:46.420
<i>[hip-hop music]</i>

07:46.422 --> 07:49.256
Okay, no one is supposed
to come close to this line.

07:49.258 --> 07:50.791
Do you understand?

07:50.793 --> 07:52.359
Everyone away.

07:52.361 --> 07:54.928
Give Miss Lillian some space
for God's sakes!

07:54.930 --> 07:56.697
No one's even coming near her.

07:56.699 --> 07:58.265
This must be some kind of mistake.

07:58.267 --> 08:00.501
I-I can't catch
the same disease as servants.

08:00.503 --> 08:02.870
I mean, we're practically
not even the same species.

08:02.872 --> 08:05.105
You don't catch a fever from a horse.

08:05.107 --> 08:06.640
You don't acquire
an immune deficiency virus

08:06.642 --> 08:09.273
from a monkey. Over the line!

08:10.479 --> 08:13.547
[crying] Everyone just leave her be!

08:13.549 --> 08:14.374
[wincing]

08:14.376 --> 08:19.353
Poor, Lillian! Poor, Lillian!

08:19.355 --> 08:23.123
<i>[gentle music]</i>

08:23.125 --> 08:25.359
Mind if I join your constitutional?

08:25.361 --> 08:28.962
- Oh, I would be delighted.
- [inhales deeply]

08:28.964 --> 08:32.566
I have to say, it's nice
to spend a moment with an adult.

08:32.568 --> 08:35.001
[chuckles] Trouble in paradise?

08:35.004 --> 08:38.205
Oh, it's Fredrick.
He can just be so childish.

08:38.554 --> 08:40.255
He doesn't know how soup works,

08:40.615 --> 08:41.842
he's convinced he's got a twin brother

08:41.844 --> 08:43.241
who lives in the mirror,

08:43.729 --> 08:45.212
he's afraid of clouds.

08:45.537 --> 08:48.148
Sometimes I wish I had met
a proper gentleman,

08:48.150 --> 08:49.413
- like yourself.
- Oh...

08:49.985 --> 08:51.790
I'm afraid I'm no gentleman.

08:52.655 --> 08:54.734
I have a confession to make, Celery.

08:55.224 --> 08:57.775
The only reason
I came out here was to...

08:58.094 --> 09:00.160
bend you over in the woods.

09:00.162 --> 09:02.763
Oh, Dick.

09:02.765 --> 09:05.332
Garfield, who are all these people?

09:05.334 --> 09:08.702
Well, that's Connie, the chef,

09:08.704 --> 09:11.238
and that's Quincy, the coal shoveler,

09:11.240 --> 09:13.941
and that's Pearl, she was your wet nurse

09:13.943 --> 09:17.377
and your primary companion for
the first 19 years of your life.

09:18.007 --> 09:19.855
Huh.

09:20.116 --> 09:22.850
And... and what about that
little woman. What does she do?

09:22.852 --> 09:24.585
She kills and plucks the egrets

09:24.587 --> 09:26.686
for the feather collars of your stoles.

09:28.924 --> 09:31.503
You mean, without her
my collar would just be...

09:31.894 --> 09:34.362
- a plain collar?
- Yes, ma'am.

09:34.764 --> 09:36.196
What about my bowel movements

09:36.198 --> 09:38.599
that magically disappear by morning?

09:38.601 --> 09:41.568
Well, I'm proud to say,
I remove those myself.

09:41.570 --> 09:43.036
But there's always a little note

09:43.038 --> 09:44.705
saying they've taken
a "stroll to Brown Town"

09:44.707 --> 09:46.573
with a caricature in a top hat.

09:46.575 --> 09:48.442
<i>♪</i> ♪

09:48.444 --> 09:49.658
Oh.

09:50.446 --> 09:53.242
All these years I knew
you were "serve-ants,"

09:53.749 --> 09:55.549
but it never occurred to me that

09:55.551 --> 09:57.684
you were "serve-people."

09:57.686 --> 09:58.919
<i>♪ Damn, damn, damn, damn, damn, damn ♪</i>

09:58.921 --> 10:00.487
<i>♪</i> Damn, son ♪

10:01.557 --> 10:03.457
both: Mmm.

10:03.459 --> 10:05.759
Double dates are so much more
fun when its just two people.

10:05.761 --> 10:07.628
Mm-hmm. And how delightful

10:07.630 --> 10:09.396
that we can be in such
a romantic setting

10:09.398 --> 10:11.098
and not even think about
getting back together?

10:11.100 --> 10:12.499
[chuckles] That's so true.

10:12.501 --> 10:14.902
- Mm-hmm.
- We are just friends now.

10:14.904 --> 10:16.035
Mm-hmm.

10:18.012 --> 10:20.546
[giggles] See? It just feels so normal.

10:20.548 --> 10:22.048
Yes, it's like playing a game of chess

10:22.050 --> 10:23.749
or being pen pals.

10:24.852 --> 10:26.452
Oh, call me Mr. Buttfingers,

10:26.454 --> 10:28.320
I've gotten chocolate
all over your face.

10:30.004 --> 10:32.271
- Shall I lick it off?
- Oh, well...

10:32.630 --> 10:34.794
- As a friend.
- I think that would be fine,

10:34.796 --> 10:37.396
- but only as a friend.
- Of course.

10:37.398 --> 10:40.199
Mm-hmm.

10:40.201 --> 10:42.301
Hmm. That felt so normal.

10:42.303 --> 10:43.636
Mm-hmm. [chuckles]

10:43.638 --> 10:45.671
It was almost like kissing, though.

10:45.673 --> 10:47.840
Oh, yes. [chuckles]

10:47.842 --> 10:49.408
Okay, I have a silly question for you.

10:49.410 --> 10:50.976
- Yes?
- Is there such a thing

10:50.978 --> 10:54.814
- as friends who kiss?
- Hmm. Sure there are.

10:54.816 --> 10:56.382
- They're called "pecking pals."
- Oh.

10:56.384 --> 10:57.917
Yes, they're all the rage in Boise.

10:57.919 --> 10:59.867
- Hmm.
- Shall we try?

11:00.254 --> 11:02.788
- I think that would be fine.
- Okay.

11:05.893 --> 11:07.226
- [laughs]
- I felt nothing.

11:07.228 --> 11:08.958
Delightful. [chuckles]

11:09.330 --> 11:10.830
Should we try once more with tongue?

11:10.832 --> 11:12.198
- Mm-hmm. Yes.
- Okay.

11:14.936 --> 11:17.336
[moaning] Oh, Dick,

11:17.338 --> 11:19.772
you're such a man. Such an adult.

11:19.774 --> 11:21.741
Oh, I'm a man, alright.

11:21.743 --> 11:23.209
Guess how many shipping concerns

11:23.211 --> 11:25.244
- I'm responsible for.
- How many?

11:25.246 --> 11:27.546
- Two.
- Oh, tell me more!

11:27.548 --> 11:30.516
Do you have important
responsibilities at your job?

11:30.518 --> 11:32.451
Oh, extremely important.

11:32.453 --> 11:34.920
I often have many people relying on me

11:34.922 --> 11:38.090
- and never have time for myself.
- [moans loudly] Don't stop!

11:38.092 --> 11:40.526
- Keep going!
- Sometimes...

11:40.528 --> 11:43.729
I work... through... lunch!

11:43.731 --> 11:44.930
[screams]

11:44.932 --> 11:48.134
<i>[hip-hop music]</i>

11:48.136 --> 11:51.070
- Ohh...
- [overlapping coughing]

11:57.111 --> 11:59.111
If I might be so bold,

11:59.113 --> 12:02.114
I hope your typhoid death
is swift and painless.

12:02.116 --> 12:04.216
- Do you have a name?
- Ethany.

12:04.707 --> 12:06.719
Oh, that's unfortunate.

12:06.721 --> 12:08.454
Better name you could've
made some friends.

12:08.456 --> 12:10.058
I'm sure you're right, Miss.

12:10.625 --> 12:12.474
Don't matter much now, though...

12:13.060 --> 12:16.862
seeing as we're gonna die soon anyway.

12:19.167 --> 12:21.947
No! No, it can't be like this!

12:22.336 --> 12:25.304
Garfield, everyone,
I want to get to know

12:25.306 --> 12:26.939
each and every one of you.

12:26.941 --> 12:29.742
And just so you know,
a rich person knowing you

12:29.744 --> 12:31.277
is as good as going to heaven.

12:31.279 --> 12:33.979
<i>[gentle music]</i>

12:33.981 --> 12:36.615
Well, the worst thing I've ever done

12:36.617 --> 12:38.617
is suck the bone marrow
out of the old bones

12:38.619 --> 12:40.252
reserved for the dogs.

12:40.254 --> 12:42.321
Not Mayor Cutie's bones!

12:42.323 --> 12:45.124
She needs that marrow
to prevent hip dysplasia!

12:46.794 --> 12:50.429
Oh, well, I forgive you,
but don't let Mayor Cutie know,

12:50.431 --> 12:52.131
she might not be as easy to forgive.

12:52.779 --> 12:57.096
I was responsible
for the great fire of 1892.

12:57.635 --> 13:00.536
That's how I lost my parents.

13:00.538 --> 13:02.880
Hush, child, you've had your turn.

13:03.241 --> 13:04.896
- Blanche?
- Huh?

13:05.611 --> 13:08.812
I-I-I don't...
I-I've never done anything.

13:08.814 --> 13:11.615
Such as I've never thrown anyone
down a flight of stairs...

13:11.617 --> 13:13.917
- for example.
- [laughing]

13:13.919 --> 13:17.821
Blanche, you're so boring.
I once stole a towel.

13:17.823 --> 13:20.657
Well, my real sin is the time...

13:20.659 --> 13:22.984
enamored with one of my coworkers...

13:23.762 --> 13:25.729
- [farts]
- Oh!

13:25.731 --> 13:28.598
- Off to make brown water.
- [stomach gurgling]

13:28.600 --> 13:30.033
Ohh!

13:31.136 --> 13:32.335
Lillian, your turn.

13:32.337 --> 13:34.638
[chuckles] My greatest sin...

13:34.640 --> 13:36.272
<i>[gentle music]</i>

13:36.274 --> 13:37.907
Is not realizing that
some of the greatest people

13:37.909 --> 13:40.410
I've ever known
were living right underneath me.

13:40.412 --> 13:42.979
[all gasp, aww]

13:42.981 --> 13:45.815
Oh, that and once I aborted a child

13:45.817 --> 13:47.647
to fit into a dress.

13:48.459 --> 13:49.691
Aww.

13:51.923 --> 13:53.656
[panting, whimpering]

13:53.658 --> 13:55.424
I'm hungry.

13:55.426 --> 13:57.626
Let's not just lay here and die.

13:57.628 --> 13:59.528
Let's prepare a last supper

13:59.530 --> 14:01.864
and eat together as friends.

14:01.866 --> 14:04.600
Yes, you heard her. Let's do it!

14:04.602 --> 14:06.435
Ethany, prepare the gruel.

14:06.437 --> 14:09.638
Flobelle, wash some spoons.

14:09.640 --> 14:12.308
- Lillian...
- Oh, Garfield.

14:12.310 --> 14:14.677
Some lines must never be crossed.

14:14.679 --> 14:17.546
Today I became your sister,
but I'll always be...

14:17.548 --> 14:20.282
- your master.
- Of course.

14:20.284 --> 14:23.352
Of course! Of course!

14:23.354 --> 14:27.823
<i>[gentle music]</i>

14:27.825 --> 14:29.587
- [exhales sharply] Mm.
- [chuckles]

14:29.640 --> 14:31.807
That is fun and it's great
and I like it.

14:31.809 --> 14:33.742
- [both laugh]
- Me, too.

14:33.744 --> 14:36.478
[sighs] But it isn't strange, is it?

14:36.480 --> 14:38.313
- Hmm?
- I mean, we had chocolate

14:38.315 --> 14:40.249
all over ourselves,
we had to get it off.

14:40.251 --> 14:43.519
Yes, it would've been strange
to have left the chocolate on.

14:43.521 --> 14:45.120
Chocolate isn't clothes.

14:45.718 --> 14:47.270
Also, we bathed together all the time

14:47.272 --> 14:48.352
- when we were babies.
- Exactly.

14:48.354 --> 14:49.920
And we're the same people
we were back then.

14:49.922 --> 14:52.456
- Mm-hmm.
- We're bathing as friends.

14:52.458 --> 14:53.938
- Bubble buddies.
- [giggles]

14:56.362 --> 14:58.529
- [deeply sighs]
- What's wrong, buddy?

14:58.531 --> 15:02.033
Oh, bathing always makes me so tense.

15:02.035 --> 15:05.036
Oh, no, now I feel tense, too.

15:05.038 --> 15:06.637
- Hmm.
- What are we going to do?

15:06.639 --> 15:10.307
Maybe a warm glass of milk
could do the trick.

15:10.309 --> 15:13.477
Oh, they're all dried up.

15:13.479 --> 15:14.979
You've been gone a long time.

15:14.981 --> 15:16.414
Hmm.

15:16.416 --> 15:17.882
Well, the only other option
that I can think of

15:17.884 --> 15:20.351
to relax me is sex, but...

15:20.353 --> 15:21.952
Hmm...

15:21.954 --> 15:24.889
Well, sex does always make me
feel more breezy.

15:24.891 --> 15:26.457
- It does, doesn't it?
- Mm-hmm.

15:26.459 --> 15:28.092
- [chuckles]
- But...

15:28.094 --> 15:31.128
- Can you fornicate as friends?
- Certainly.

15:31.130 --> 15:33.049
Yeah, but as long
as it's just as friends.

15:33.051 --> 15:34.432
Yes, just as friends.

15:34.434 --> 15:36.901
- Coitus colleagues.
- I think I've heard of that.

15:36.903 --> 15:38.069
I think I've heard of that, too.

15:38.094 --> 15:40.103
- Yeah.
- Okay.

15:41.641 --> 15:44.608
<i>[hip-hop music]</i>

15:44.610 --> 15:45.843
<i>♪</i> ♪

15:47.280 --> 15:49.847
Usually I eat every 35 minutes.

15:49.849 --> 15:51.749
This has been really hard.

15:51.751 --> 15:54.251
For you, Miss. I would be honored

15:54.253 --> 15:56.921
if this were to be
my last Earthly chore.

15:56.923 --> 15:58.856
Thank you, girl.

15:58.858 --> 16:00.681
So this is gruel.

16:00.683 --> 16:02.498
Never had gruel before, but...

16:09.635 --> 16:10.850
Tastes amazing.

16:11.304 --> 16:13.402
Overwhelming amount of menthol...

16:14.240 --> 16:15.297
Mm.

16:16.008 --> 16:17.808
It's like cigarette milk!

16:17.810 --> 16:20.044
[laughter]

16:20.046 --> 16:22.546
- ♪ Hello ♪
- ♪ Bonjour ♪

16:22.548 --> 16:25.816
♪ Wie geht's ♪

16:25.818 --> 16:27.485
Oh, shit.

16:27.487 --> 16:33.412
- [all singing]
- ♪ Around the world with hello ♪

16:33.414 --> 16:36.227
Good morrow servants and servant ladies,

16:36.229 --> 16:38.229
we are the Gentlemen Callers
and we are here

16:38.231 --> 16:40.164
to entertain and delight you

16:40.166 --> 16:42.533
as you push off across the River Styx.

16:42.535 --> 16:45.503
Oh, Lillian.

16:45.505 --> 16:47.972
- You're here?
- Hard cheese indeed.

16:47.974 --> 16:49.406
Awkward. Awkward moments.

16:49.408 --> 16:51.575
Well, so, the short version,

16:51.577 --> 16:54.678
every barber shop organization
has a front man.

16:54.680 --> 16:56.046
And despite the harmony in our voices,

16:56.048 --> 16:58.015
there's actually discord
as to who among us

16:58.017 --> 16:59.850
should be that front man.

16:59.852 --> 17:02.887
So we shall audition for you
and you shall cast your vote.

17:02.889 --> 17:06.022
You the work-a-day, lack-witted,

17:06.025 --> 17:07.657
unwashed and currently dying.

17:07.660 --> 17:09.425
- [clears throat]
- To give you an idea

17:09.428 --> 17:11.060
- of my background...
- First of all, no one knows...

17:11.063 --> 17:12.396
- I would like to...
- No, they...

17:12.397 --> 17:14.098
- Probably, because...
- No, no, no.

17:14.099 --> 17:15.199
I feel like it's only fair
that the baritone go first.

17:15.201 --> 17:17.067
[overlapping arguing]

17:17.069 --> 17:19.036
- Excuse me?
- What is it, child?

17:19.038 --> 17:21.372
Maybe I could sing, sirs?

17:21.374 --> 17:22.906
<i>[gentle music]</i>

17:22.909 --> 17:27.344
♪ Amazing grace ♪

17:27.346 --> 17:32.216
♪ How sweet the sound ♪

17:32.218 --> 17:36.887
♪ That saved a wretch ♪

17:36.889 --> 17:40.624
♪ Like me ♪

17:40.626 --> 17:43.260
[men laughing]

17:43.262 --> 17:45.296
Oh, sorry, I know
you're all having a moment.

17:45.298 --> 17:47.898
Here's my thing.
For me, I wanted to hear

17:47.900 --> 17:52.603
the music, but all I heard
was you trying so hard.

17:52.605 --> 17:54.205
- Ugh.
- These are actually...

17:54.207 --> 17:56.140
I ha... I actually have tears of hatred.

17:56.142 --> 17:57.908
Bad. Bad news all around.

17:57.910 --> 17:59.777
With all due respect,
I think that's perhaps

17:59.779 --> 18:01.979
why we are talented musicians

18:01.981 --> 18:04.148
and you are dying of typhoid.

18:04.150 --> 18:06.417
- [coughing]
- Read the room next time.

18:06.419 --> 18:08.319
Just read the room.
'Cause you killed this room.

18:08.321 --> 18:09.753
This side of the room is dying.

18:09.755 --> 18:13.224
Oh, no! Someone... Someone get a doctor!

18:13.226 --> 18:14.925
Jaunt away. Jaunt away!

18:14.927 --> 18:16.594
Jaunt! Jaunt! Jaunt! Jaunt!

18:16.596 --> 18:18.796
We're all gonna die!

18:18.798 --> 18:21.765
<i>[sultry music]</i>

18:21.767 --> 18:27.638
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:27.640 --> 18:29.340
Tell me your five-year plan!

18:29.342 --> 18:31.542
It... involves... diversification.

18:31.544 --> 18:33.277
- Don't look away.
- I won't.

18:33.279 --> 18:34.979
- Don't look away.
- I never look away.

18:34.981 --> 18:37.047
- Yes!
- You eat dirt.

18:37.049 --> 18:38.782
You eat dirt. That's a dirty girl.

18:38.784 --> 18:40.417
[both softly moaning]

18:40.419 --> 18:42.419
[both grunting, moaning]

18:42.421 --> 18:44.154
[both softly moaning]

18:44.156 --> 18:45.756
Aah!

18:45.758 --> 18:49.026
- [screams] Oh. Oh, my God.
- [sighs]

18:49.028 --> 18:50.995
- Whoo, that's good.
- That was good.

18:50.997 --> 18:53.464
[crying]

18:53.466 --> 18:56.367
[dishes clanging]

18:57.470 --> 19:00.064
Get water. She needs water.

19:01.007 --> 19:03.274
[grunting]

19:03.276 --> 19:06.377
Attention, I bring the doctor with news.

19:06.379 --> 19:08.812
Right, how is everyone feeling?

19:08.814 --> 19:10.614
- [groans]
- Don't know why I ask.

19:10.616 --> 19:13.550
I could've asked my nose. [laughing]

19:14.987 --> 19:17.688
[scattered laughter]

19:17.690 --> 19:21.458
So, good news,
you just have food poisoning.

19:21.460 --> 19:24.028
It's pretty uncomfortable,
but not fatal at all.

19:24.030 --> 19:26.397
[all exclaim]

19:26.399 --> 19:29.199
So you're all going to live.

19:29.201 --> 19:31.702
I've already taken the liberty
of burning your possessions

19:31.704 --> 19:34.038
as a precaution and I'm docking you each

19:34.040 --> 19:37.107
a month's worth of pay
for laying about on the job.

19:37.109 --> 19:38.734
Back to work!

19:39.245 --> 19:41.145
<i>[gentle music]</i>

19:41.147 --> 19:44.048
And, Miss, in spite of my terrible name,

19:44.050 --> 19:47.318
I did make a friend and her name...

19:47.320 --> 19:48.919
is Lillian.

19:50.496 --> 19:53.464
<i>[soft string music]</i>

19:53.466 --> 19:54.565
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:54.567 --> 19:55.900
Oh.

19:57.937 --> 20:01.939
Oh, dear, how I've missed you.

20:01.941 --> 20:03.841
What have you two been up to

20:03.843 --> 20:05.309
since we were gone?

20:05.311 --> 20:07.978
- Oh, just friend stuff.
- Yes.

20:07.980 --> 20:09.747
- Us, too.
- Oh!

20:09.749 --> 20:11.181
- How wonderful.
- [chuckles]

20:11.183 --> 20:13.317
Thank God we can all be friends.

20:13.319 --> 20:14.486
Mm-hmm.

20:15.021 --> 20:17.488
I never realized how easy
being friends is.

20:17.490 --> 20:19.924
Now I can have Fredrick and Dick.

20:19.926 --> 20:22.026
<i>[hip-hop music]</i>

20:22.028 --> 20:23.093
<i>♪ Bitch ♪</i>

20:23.095 --> 20:25.329
- [bell dings]
- Ethany!

20:25.331 --> 20:27.631
- [bell dings]
- Ethany!

20:27.633 --> 20:29.033
Yes, ma'am?

20:29.035 --> 20:31.001
Ethany, remember that meal we shared?

20:31.003 --> 20:33.771
Well, I've developed a bit
of a taste for that fever gruel.

20:33.773 --> 20:35.372
Would you go fetch me a bowl?

20:35.374 --> 20:36.608
Yes, ma'am.

20:37.209 --> 20:40.414
Oh, and, girl, make it two bowls.

20:41.136 --> 20:43.213
One for me and one for yourself.

20:43.350 --> 20:45.289
Yes, ma'am!

20:45.985 --> 20:47.985
- Oh, girl.
- Yes, ma'am?

20:47.987 --> 20:50.807
Actually, I'll take both bowls.

20:51.290 --> 20:52.723
I'm really hungry.

20:52.725 --> 20:54.458
<i>- [deflated]
- Yes, ma'am.</i>
